# Task Group Definition Policy

When the user specifies new task groups/tasks, follow this policy by default:

1. Define them via the existing task template framework:
   - `TASK_GROUP_TEMPLATE` + `TASK_TEMPLATE`
   - no ad-hoc runtime-only group/task definitions for feature logic
2. Persist definitions in core seed data in the same change set:
   - add/update core datasets under `backend/app/seed/datasets/core/`
   - ensure core loader registration under `backend/app/seed/loaders/core/` and `backend/app/seed/__init__.py`
3. Consume and render them through the usual configurable TaskBoard flow:
   - avoid introducing custom one-off task UIs when TaskBoard can represent the workflow
   - reuse existing task filtering/visibility mechanisms instead of bespoke task handling

## Implementation Notes

- Keep task template keys stable and English.
- Use deterministic offsets (`offset_minutes_default`) for due-date semantics.
- If sample seed also overrides templates in DEV, mirror new core templates there to prevent drift.
